Defendant Chad Douglass Verzella in court with attorney Mark A. Pecora.  Deann L Heard appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for sentencing hearing. Parties are prepared to proceed. Statements made as to sentencing. Court finds the State has complied with the victim rights legislation.

As to COUNT 1-
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 48 MONTHS, with credit for 1 day time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 24 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 24 MONTHS.  

Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program. The defendant is NOT eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 30 MONTHS with the following conditions:

1) Court ordered 6 MONTHS of condition time in the House of Correction, FORTHWITH. Defendant may have release for work, the Day Reporting Center, and vocational/education programming. Court costs, fees, surcharges, and restitution to be paid through collection by the House of Correction from 25% of funds/wages.
2) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge;
3) Pay all costs, fees, surcharges and restitution during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
4) No contact with Marshall Erecting Inc. or the premises of Marshall Erecting Inc.;
5) AODA assessment and comply with any recommended treatment or counseling;
6) Mental health evaluation and comply with any recommended treatment or therapy. Court will allow the therapy defendant is already participating in to satisfy the Court's order;
7) Provide prescription medications to agent before filling them;
8) Maintain absolute sobriety;
9) Random urine screens;
10) Pay restitution in the amount of $7,864.97. $1,000.00 to be paid to Marshall Erecting Inc. The remaining amount of $6,864.97 to be paid to Western National Mutual Insurance Company. Restitution to be paid FIRST before all costs, fees and surcharges. 

Court ordered a restitution hearing date be set to determine the remaining amounts of restitution. 

If revoked, court costs, fees, surcharges and restitution be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds/wages. 

It is the Court's intention that the conditions of probation be the same conditions for extended supervision if revoked. 

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
Filed;
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit.  Restitution hearing scheduled for October 8, 2015 at 08:30 am.
